    "description": "Marcus Aurelius Antoninus (/\u0254\u02d0\u02c8ri\u02d0li\u0259s/ or-EE-lee-\u0259s; Latin: [\u02c8ma\u02d0rk\u028as au\u032f\u02c8re\u02d0li.us anto\u02d0\u02c8ni\u02d0n\u028as]; 26 April 121 \u2013 17 March 180) was Roman emperor from 161 to 180 and a Stoic philosopher. He was a member of the Nerva\u2013Antonine dynasty, the last of the rulers later known as the Five Good Emperors and the last emperor of the Pax Romana, an age of relative peace, calm, and stability for the Roman Empire lasting from 27 BC to 180 AD. He served as Roman consul in 140, 145, and 161.",
